## Bio

I am a Computer Scientist living in Cambridge (UK). 
My research currently focuses on using short-read transcriptomic data to understand RNA splicing changes in human disease, with a special focus in neurodegeneration. But, of course, I also love talking about cats, music and philosophy.


## Education

**University College London** | London, UK

Ph.D. in Human Transcriptomics | August 2019 - Oct 2023

**University of Murcia** | Murcia, Spain

MS.c. in Artificial Intelligence | September 2017 - May 2018

**University Miguel Hernandez, Elche** | Alicante, Spain

B.S. in Computer Science | September 2010 - May 2014


